adjectives.description: incompatible (comparative more incompatible, superlative most incompatible)

entries.meaning: Of two things: that cannot coexist; not congruous because of differences; unable to function together due to dissimilarities.
examples: My phone is incompatible with the latest version of this app.

entries.meaning: (chemistry) Incapable of being together without mutual reaction or decomposition, as certain medicines.

(medicine, chemistry, chiefly in the plural) An incompatible substance; one of a group of things that cannot be placed or used together because of a change of chemical composition or opposing medicinal qualities.

examples: Incompatibles are consequents of contraries. For example, sleeping and waking are contraries, and snoring is associated with sleepers. So snoring and waking are incompatibles.
